{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The clause extractor identifies all key terms (parties, dates, obligations, penalties) present in the contract.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model extraction quality over varied legal phrasing; mocked extractor outputs would hide misses in recall, especially for ambiguous wording and long-context contracts.","test_description":"Run the real clause-extractor model on a gold-labeled set of real contracts and assert per-document recall for parties/dates/obligations/penalties meets threshold; include hard paraphrased and nested-clause cases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk assessor flags language that would be problematic under the configured risk policy, even when the problematic phrasing is indirect or euphemistic.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is semantic judgment quality, not just wiring. Mocked or rule-only tests can pass while the real model misses euphemistic/indirect risk language.","test_description":"Evaluate the real risk-assessor model against a labeled corpus containing explicit and euphemistic risky clauses under the active policy; assert target precision/recall and include repeated runs to detect instability on borderline text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.09}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The compliance checker correctly determines whether the contract meets all applicable regulatory requirements for the configured jurisdiction.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Determination quality depends on model interpretation of legal text against jurisdiction-specific requirements; mocks can validate plumbing but miss real misclassification behavior.","test_description":"Run the real compliance-check model on jurisdiction-tagged, expert-labeled contracts (compliant/non-compliant with rationale) and assert decision accuracy and required citation coverage for each jurisdiction.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments (e.g., extractor says \"standard\" but risk assessor says \"high risk\"), the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure boundary is cross-module schema and merge logic interaction (normalization, keying, attribution fields). A pure unit mock of one function can miss contract between reviewer-output adapters and merger.","test_description":"Feed merger through actual reviewer-output parsers/adapters using fixture payloads with clause-ID collisions and conflicting labels; assert unified report retains both assessments with correct reviewer attribution and no overwrite.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end multi-agent pipeline with parallel agentic steps plus merge/orchestration. Failures can emerge only when real model outputs, concurrency, collection, and merge interact.","test_description":"Execute the production pipeline on real contracts with all three real reviewers in parallel, then verify final report contains traceable findings from each reviewer and preserves conflicts; include timeout/retry observation and run multiple times to catch nondeterministic drop/ordering issues.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.18,"Workflow":0.72}}]}
